JOHANNESBURG, November 26 – Football legend Mike Magena, 58, who was arrested after a drug manufacturing bust on his property last week, was granted R50,000 bail on Monday at the Randfontein Magistrate’s Court. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Lungelo Dlamini said the famous former striker was taken in by police for questioning as he owns the property on which the drug lab was found. Dlamini added that a police crime intelligence investigation led to the raiding of the house.  (ANA) Former soccer star, Mike “Sporo” Mangena arrested for drugs in Hillside, Randfontein 